    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_3398125811" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3398125811" />
    <a title="Grace" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/34465556-grace"><img alt="Grace" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1588296669p2/34465556.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3398125811?book_show_action=true">Jun 21, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Grace" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Grace" href="/user/show/34465556-grace">Grace</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/34465556-grace?shelf=pub-1800s">pub-1800s</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/34465556-grace?shelf=classics">classics</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/34465556-grace?shelf=horror">horror</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/34465556-grace?shelf=r-horrorlit-bingo-2020">r-horrorlit-bingo-2020</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/34465556-grace?shelf=read-2020">read-2020</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/34465556-grace?shelf=owned-ebook">owned-ebook</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/34465556-grace?shelf=fantasy">fantasy</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/34465556-grace?shelf=vampires">vampires</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3398125811" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8966238393192693801"><i>Carmilla</i> was actually written prior to and was an inspiration for Bram Stoker’s <i>Dracula</i>. That was how I first heard about this novella. I read the Wikipedia article about it and found many of the details fascinating—the evil vampire is female, and has the ability to turn into a cat. So, I decided to pick this up and read it before digging in to <i>Dracula</i>, and also just because I’m a sucker for vampire fiction. <br/><br/><b>Actual Rating: 4.2</b><br/><br/>This went by surprisingly quickly. I think that’s partially because of</span>
  <span id="freeText8966238393192693801" style="display:none"><i>Carmilla</i> was actually written prior to and was an inspiration for Bram Stoker’s <i>Dracula</i>. That was how I first heard about this novella. I read the Wikipedia article about it and found many of the details fascinating—the evil vampire is female, and has the ability to turn into a cat. So, I decided to pick this up and read it before digging in to <i>Dracula</i>, and also just because I’m a sucker for vampire fiction. <br /><br /><b>Actual Rating: 4.2</b><br /><br />This went by surprisingly quickly. I think that’s partially because of its length and the fact that I didn’t realize it was so short and partially because there was never a dull moment. There was simply no time to get bored. <br /><br />Due to the length of the novella, there wasn’t much time to have a large cast of characters. Instead, Le Fanu focuses on developing those that are present—namely, Laura, Laura’s father, and Carmilla herself. I felt like this was done well, but there was a little something lacking. I suspect this is because there are social cues and circumstances that I’m not picking up on since this was written in the nineteenth century. The writing style itself, however, was perfectly fine. <br /><br />My only regret is that I would have liked to learn a little bit more about vampires. Or, perhaps more specific information about what we are told. <br /><br /><blockquote>
  <i>”Love will have it’s sacrifices. No sacrifice without blood.”</i>
</blockquote><br /><br />Regardless, <i>Carmilla</i> is a must-read for anyone who loves vampires—especially anyone who loves reading about them as much as I do.</span>
  <a data-text-id="8966238393192693801" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


